## Risk levels (reference)

| Level | Examples |
|---|---|
| Low | read-only search, summarization |
| Medium | drafting files, creating tickets |
| High | sending email, modifying repos, running shell |
| Critical | deleting data, spending money, changing permissions |

## Restricted (never, without explicit user request)
- {{e.g., `git push --force`, `rm -rf`}}
- {{...}}

## Failure handling
- Tool errors must be returned as structured `{ "error": "...", "retryable": bool }`
- After {{N=2}} retries on the same tool, surface the error and stop
- Never silently swallow tool failures

## Approval mechanism
Approvals are requested via {{mechanism — e.g., "writing to `logs/approvals/pending.json` and pausing the run"}}. Auto-approval on timeout is **not allowed**.
